\section{ABOUT}
Dr. Tao Ge is a researcher in GenAI/LLMs, currently leading post-training of frontier models, with foundational innovations spanning synthetic data, low-cost GenAI, and agentic approaches:
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=1.3em, itemsep=0.2em]
    \item \textbf{Post-training of OpenAI Frontier Models} (2025-): Tao leads end-to-end post-training of OpenAI frontier models (\textbf{GPT-5.4/5.4 mini}), leveraging proprietary innovations in synthetic data, training algorithms and graders\textsuperscript{\ref{pub:docreward}} to optimize Microsoft 365 productivity scenarios. The resulting models achieve state-of-the-art performance across a comprehensive suite of productivity benchmarks — including a \textbf{79\% win-or-tie rate} over the state-of-the-art (base) GPT-5.4 model on GDPVal — and serve hundreds of millions of M365 Copilot users worldwide.

    \item \textbf{Persona-Driven Synthetic Data Creation} (2024): Tao invented a new paradigm for scaling synthetic data generation with \textbf{billions of diverse personas\textsuperscript{\ref{pub:persona}}}, addressing a fundamental bottleneck of synthetic data — the lack of diversity and coverage — and enabling scalable data synthesis across training, evaluation, and user/world simulation for agentic scenarios. This approach has been widely adopted for development of leading LLMs and agentic environments, including OLMo/Molmo (\companylogo{ai2}\,AI2), Nemotron (\companylogo{nvidia}\,Nvidia), Qwen (\companylogo{alibaba}\,Alibaba), ARE/GAIA2 (\companylogo{meta}\,Meta), Hunyuan (\companylogo{tencent}\,Tencent), LongCat (\companylogo{meituan}\,Meituan), PaddlePaddle (\companylogo{baidu}\,Baidu), SmolLM (\companylogo{huggingface}\,Huggingface), Hermes (\companylogo{nousresearch}\,NousResearch), Minicpm (\companylogo{modelbest}\,Modelbest).
    \item \textbf{Speculative Decoding} (2021--2023): Tao pioneered seminal work on Speculative Decoding, beginning with a \textbf{drafter-free} formulation with predicted outputs in 2021\textsuperscript{\ref{pub:aggressive}} and then extending it to a more \textbf{general drafter-verifier framework} in early 2022\textsuperscript{\ref{pub:specdec}}, which was \textbf{\textcolor{red}{the first}} (\href{https://arxiv.org/pdf/2203.16487v1}{Mar 2022}) to introduce a separate drafter model for lossless Transformer inference acceleration, \textbf{\textcolor{red}{the first}} (\href{https://openreview.net/forum?id=H-VlwsYvVi}{Sep 2022}) to coin the term ``Speculative Decoding'' for this paradigm, and \textbf{\textcolor{red}{the first}} (\href{https://github.com/microsoft/unilm/tree/master/decoding}{May 2022}) to open-source the (drafter--verifier) decoding paradigm. Tao's research was subsequently followed by Google (Nov 2022) and DeepMind (Feb 2023) for LLM acceleration, which has become an industry standard since 2023, integrated into major frameworks such as vLLM, PyTorch, and ONNX, and is widely used in production deployments. In addition, Tao's methodology on \textbf{speculative decoding with predicted outputs} proposed in 2021\textsuperscript{\ref{pub:aggressive}} and early 2023\textsuperscript{\ref{pub:llma}} was adopted by OpenAI in its \href{https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/predicted-outputs}{Predicted Outputs} feature.
\end{itemize}

